articles.description: Emmanuel Ndumanya scored a career-high 23 points, pulled down 10 rebounds and Josip Vrankic tossed in 19 points in Santa Clara's 81-72 win at Portland Thursday night.
articles.headline: Ndumanya scores 23 as Santa Clara holds off Portland 81-72

articles.description: Elijah Bryant scored nine of his 25 points in overtime and BYU held off upset-minded Pepperdine 75-70.
articles.headline: Bryant helps BYU holds off Pepperdine 75-70 in OT

articles.description: Michael Onyebalu had 24 points, Siler Schneider scored 16 and Rogers Printup added 15 points as UC Davis outlasted Cal Poly 92-84 in triple overtime on Thursday night.
articles.headline: UC Davis outlasts Cal Poly in triple overtime 92-84

articles.description: Brayon Blake had 24 points with 14 rebounds and Victor Sanders added 21 points as Idaho battled back late to beat Montana State 88-78 and win its fifth straight Big Sky Conference game Thursday night.
articles.headline: Idaho rallies to beat Montana State for 5th straight win

articles.description: Leland King II scored 20 points and grabbed 15 rebounds, Gabe Vincent added 19 points, and UC Santa Barbara pulled ahead early to beat Long Beach State 80-70 on Thursday night to remain atop the Big West Conference standings.
articles.headline: UC Santa Barbara beats Long Beach St 80-70

articles.description: Taveion Hollingsworth tossed in 30 points and Darius Thompson scored nine of his 28 points in overtime to lift Western Kentucky to a 102-94 victory over North Texas on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Western Kentucky fends off North Texas 102-94 in OT

videos.description: Trevon Duval hooks in a shot on a tough drive and draw the foul for Duke.
videos.headline: Duval goes up strong for and-1

videos.description: Kenny Williams knocks down a 3-pointer to tie the game for the Tar Heels and Luke Maye puts them ahead quickly afterwards on a fast-break layup.
videos.headline: UNC swings back in front

videos.description: Marques Bolden gets the ball in the paint and spins to finish with his left hand for Duke.
videos.headline: Bolden spins for the finish

videos.description: Trevon Duval finds a hole in the defense and throws down an emphatic dunk for Duke.
videos.headline: Duval soars down the lane for a massive jam

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (Duval soars down the lane for a massive jam) 2018/02/08 ESHEET

videos.description: Gary Trent Jr. knocks down an easy 3-pointer for the Blue Devils to go up 31-24.
videos.headline: Trent Jr. left all alone for 3

videos.description: Grayson Allen floats a pass to Wendell Carter Jr. who slams it home for the Duke alley-oop.
videos.headline: Allen finds Carter for the oop

videos.description: UNC's Theo Pinson extends for the block setting up Cameron Johnson for the fast-break finish.
videos.headline: Pinson's block leads to UNC fast-break bucket

videos.description: Cameron Johnson knocks down a 3-pointer but it is quickly met by Alex O'Connell who hits one of his own.
videos.headline: UNC and Duke trading 3s

videos.description: Grayson Allen tries to get in front of Luke Maye for a charge and comes up holding his right wrist before the half.
videos.headline: Allen holding wrist after taking spill

videos.description: Theo Pinson gets the ball from Marvin Bagley III leading to a hectic sequence finished off by a hook shot from Cameron Johnson.
videos.headline: Pinson's steal puts UNC back in front

videos.description: Kenny Williams puts the Tar Heels up 5 with his fifth 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Williams hits another 3 for UNC

videos.description: Marvin Bagley III gets the ball in the paint and loses his man to spin for the Blue Devil dunk.
videos.headline: Bagley spins for open dunk

videos.description: Kenny Williams knocks down his sixth 3-pointer of the night, followed by a buzzer beater 3-pointer from Wendell Carter Jr.
videos.headline: Williams, Carter Jr. exchange 3s

videos.description: Marvin Bagley III blocks a dunk attempt from Garrison Brooks keeping it a 3-point game.
videos.headline: Bagley denies Brooks at the rim

videos.description: Cameron Johnson knocks down a 3-pointer to put the Tar Heels up 77-71 with just over 3 minutes to play.
videos.headline: Johnson extends UNC's lead with 3-pointer

videos.description: The No. 21 Tar Heels go on a 14-0 run in the second half and get 21 points from Joel Berry II in an 82-78 win over the No. 9 Blue Devils.
videos.headline: UNC uses big second half to topple Duke

tracking.trackingName: NCB_One-Play (UNC uses big second half to topple Duke) 2018/02/08 ESHEET SOTFULL

videos.description: Kenny Williams scores 20 points, sinking six 3-pointers, and Cameron Johnson adds 18 points as No. 21 Tar Heels defeats No. 9 Duke 82-78.
videos.headline: UNC fends off Duke

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCB Highlight (UNC fends off Duke) 2018/02/08 2018/02/08 ESHEET

videos.description: Dan Shulman and Jay Bilas break down how Joel Berry II and Kenny Williams stepped up to take down the No. 9 Blue Devils at home as the No. 21 Tar Heels win 82-78.
videos.headline: Berry, Williams lead UNC over Duke

videos.description: Kenny Williams and Cameron Johnson combine to score 38 points to help the No. 21 Tar Heels defeat their biggest rivals.
videos.headline: UNC takes Round 1 from Duke
